The hard drive stores all software and data saved to it. The purpose of a hard drive is to store data permanently and to be accessible when using the system.

What is the difference between the master and slave hard drive configuration? How is the hard drive configured to master or slave?

The purpose of using master and slave drives is that it allows for two dives on the same cable.

A master drive is the main bootable drive, this is plugged directly into the IDE cable from the motherboard. The most common way a master and slave configuration is used is to use a Solid State Drive (SSD) as the master drive, and the Hard Disk Drive (HDD) as a slave drive.
